CHOLERA - SRI LANKA (08)
************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
See Also
Cholera - Sri Lanka (05) 980909004714
Cholera - Sri Lanka (06) 980911230522
Cholera - Sri Lanka (07) 980919170231
Date: Wed, 14 Oct 1998 09:34:59 -0500
Source: Daily News from Lakehouse Sri Lanka 10/14 [excerpts
Via: Clyde Markon <docmarkon@worldnet.att.net>

One cholera patient has died at the Madhu Hospital from among 33 suspected
cases admitted since October 5, Medecines Sans Frontiers (MSF) Head of
Mission Eric Cerciat told the Daily News yesterday. Meanwhile, the
Pallamadu cholera centre in Mannar has treated 41 patients during the same
period, he said. Since September end five cholera patients have died, in
Pallamadu.
"The number of cholera patients have increased since September. We have
made arrangements to bring the situation under control," Mr. Cerciat said.
MSF is an international NGO which offers medical assistance to population
in distress, victims of natural or man-made disasters and victims of armed
conflict. The Group has been in Sri Lanka since 1996 working in Batticaloa,
Vavuniya, Jaffna and Madhu.
[Written by: Chandani Jayatilleke
